.TH eroosterctl-version 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-version \- display version and build information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl version
[\fI\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the eroosterctl version number and the database backend compiled into
this binary (\fBpostgres\fR or \fBsqlite\fR). This command does not require
the configuration file and exits without connecting to any external service.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fBjson\fR
Emit a JSON object with \fIversion\fR and \fIdb_backend\fR fields.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
eroosterctl version
# eroosterctl 0.1.0
# DB backend:  postgres

eroosterctl --output json version
# {"version":"0.1.0","db_backend":"postgres"}
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\fR(1)
